Key Match Events: Julius Randle had 23 points and 10 rebounds, Anthony Edwards added 21 points and seven assists.
Naz Reid came off the bench to score 16 points, and Rudy Gobert added 10 points and 12 rebounds for Minnesota.
Goga Bitadze led Orlando with 15 points and eight rebounds. Kentavious Caldwell-Pope added 13 points.
Timberwolves led from the middle of the first quarter and by 24 at one point.

Edwards launched himself over the Magic's Anthony Black for a dunk, then came down with a glare at the crowd to give the Wolves a 10-point lead with 3:19 left in the third quarter. They led by double figures for the rest of the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Timberwolves broke a seven-game losing streak against Eastern Conference opponents.
The Magic shot 38% and is now the lowest-scoring team in the NBA at 104.8 points per game.
It may have been the last of 34 games without Paolo Banchero, who is expected to return Friday night.
In the middle of the fourth quarter, the Timberwolves were 12 for 28 (43%) from 3-point range while the Magic were 6 for 30 (20%).
